data.enText: an Anglican priest who is in charge of a church and the area around it (called a parish )
a priest in the US Episcopal Church

tr: a Roman Catholic priest who acts for another higher-ranking clergyman
(Church of England) a clergyman appointed to act as priest of a parish
(Episcopal Church) a clergyman in charge of a chapel

value.def: A vicar is an Anglican priest who is in charge of a church and the area it is in, which is called a parish.
value.tran: （英国国教的）教区牧师，教区教堂主持

value.def: A vicar is a priest who is in charge of a chapel that is associated with a parish church in the Episcopal Church in the United States.
value.tran: （美国新教圣公会的）教堂主持,教区牧师
